actions: section header in modul: Page history: context user actions
actions_admin: section header in modul: Page history: context actions made by administrators
all: selection menu e.g. all namespaces in modul: Pages created
approve: Name of a MediaWiki log action, used as header of a row in the table of log action counts for a user
approximate: addition in braces, to indicate that these figures are inaccurate
article: label for a wiki page in main namespace
atbe: Average time between edits by a single user
autoedits: (semi-)automated edits with known tools like huggle
average_change_per_page: Average change (in bytes) the user has made on a page
average_change_per_page_sign: message with Ø-sign, average change per page
average_per_page_sign: message with Ø-sign, avarage edits per page
avg_edits_per_time_sign: label with Ø-sign, $1 = unit (day, month, year), unit is always singular
avg_timebwedits_sign: label with Ø-sign, the average time between two edits
block: Name of a MediaWiki log action, used as header of a row in the table of log action counts for a user
bottomninety: chart label, as short as possible
bytes: label for single character, plural, eg. text length = 3455 bytes
delete: Name of a MediaWiki log action, used as header of a row in the table of log action counts for a user
editorcount: Number of editors per page, phrase as short as possible
edits_summary: Edits with provided edit summary line
end: menu option to limit the search
events: Events that have a log entry
generalstats: section header of section main figures
highreplag: error if database replication is high
import: Name of a MediaWiki log action, used as header of a row in the table of log action counts for a user
ips: label for non-logged in users, plural
limit: option to specify a limit of results
live: Live edits, visible edits of a user
mainspace: common name for main namespace in this wiki eg: (en)Article, (de) Artikel
maxadd: Maximun text added by a user, short word or abbreviation for Max. (if possible)
maxdel: Maximum text deleted by a user, short word or abbreviation for Max. (if possible)
million: message of success; preserved for archiving purposes :-) {{Notranslate}}
neutral: exact term for neutral on vote pages
no_summary: chart label for edits without summary, short phrase
nofollowredir: form option eg. in modul: Page history
nograph2: message log in: $1 = OAuth help link
noresult: error: No matching results found for: $1 = search term
numedits: Number of edits a user has made
oppose: exact term for oppose on vote pages
others: label in chart for the rest
past_time: time period addition in braces $1 = number, $2 = unit (days, minutes), eg: Statistics (past 365 days)
patrol: Name of a MediaWiki log action, used as header of a row in the table of log action counts for a user
protect: Name of a MediaWiki log action, used as header of a row in the table of log action counts for a user
redirects: wiki pages that redirect to other pages (short word)
redirfilter_all: form option in modul: Pages created
redirfilter_noredirects: form option in modul: Pages created
redirfilter_onlyredirects: form option in modul: Pages created
restore: Name of a MediaWiki log action, used as header of a row in the table of log action counts for a user
resultbyname: label for results by name or IP
rfx_bureaucrat: further intro message in modul: RfX
rfx_intro: This sentence is followed by a list of configured sites
see_full_edit_counts: label for a link to further details
see_full_page_stats: label for a link to further details
select_language: link to select the GUI language
start: menu option to limit the search
support: exact term for support on vote pages
tagged: in the context that something is marked, eg. a minor edit is tagged (m)
thank: Name of a MediaWiki log action, used as header of a row in the table of log action counts for a user
time_ago: $1 = number, $2 = unit (minutes, days) ago; e.g: last update: 30 minutes ago
timebwedits: the average time between two edits
timecard: Chart that shows the edit behaviour
tool_adminstats: Top menu title: short phrase! or shortcut (to fit into the design) or leave untranslated
tool_articleinfo: Top menu title: short phrase! or shortcut (to fit into the design) or leave untranslated
tool_autoedits: Top menu title: short phrase! or shortcut (to fit into the design) or leave untranslated

tool_blame: Top menu title: short phrase! or shortcut (to fit into the design) or leave untranslated
tool_ec: Top menu title: short phrase! or shortcut (to fit into the design) or leave untranslated
tool_pages: Top menu title: short phrase! or shortcut (to fit into the design) or leave untranslated
tool_rfa: Top menu title: short phrase! or shortcut (to fit into the design) or leave untranslated
tool_rfap: Top menu title: short phrase! or shortcut (to fit into the design) or leave untranslated
tool_sc: Top menu title: short phrase! or shortcut (to fit into the design) or leave untranslated
tool_topedits: Top menu title: short phrase! or shortcut (to fit into the design) or leave untranslated
topeditedpages: Top edited pages oof a user
topten: chart label, as short as possible
toptenbyedits: chart label for TOP 10 by edits
toptenbytext: chart label for TOP 10 by added text
unapprove: Name of a MediaWiki log action, used as header of a row in the table of log action counts for a user
unblock: Name of a MediaWiki log action, used as header of a row in the table of log action counts for a user
unknown: neither support nor oppose nor neutral
unprotect: Name of a MediaWiki log action, used as header of a row in the table of log action counts for a user
userid: registration id of a user (short term)
vote_msg: $1 =username, $2 = number, $3 = name of vote page eg: Requests for adminship
with_summary: chart label for edits with summary, short phrase
